<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-21T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 183.9 Brazil/2:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-21T20:00:00-05:00">December 21, 1918—8 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 22—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>89. For the Secretary of State. Embassy, Rio de Janeiro, urgently
                            requests information as to how invitations to Peace Conference will be
                            issued and whether less important Allied countries such as Brazil may
                            participate on their own invitation. Embassy also states that The
                            Chamber of Deputies have asked Brazilian Minister of Foreign Office
                            whether Brazil has been invited. <persName corresp="#p_DGD1">Da
                                Gama</persName> sent personal message to me stating he would be very
                            much embarrassed by his inability to answer inquiries and asked for your
                            friendly assistance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>